[psutil](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/psutil#downloads) provides an abstract interface to process related API. It&#39;s a cross-platform library allows you retrieve the processes and system running state information such as CPU, memory, disk usage, network, etc. It&#39;s a great tool for system monitoring and administration.

```
import psutil
 
for proc in psutil.process_iter():
    print(proc.name())
 
def kill_by_process_name(name):
    for proc in psutil.process_iter():
        if proc.name() == name:
            print(&quot;Killing process: &quot; + name)
            if(check_process_exist_by_name(name)):
                print(&quot;Killing process: &quot; + name + &quot; sucess&quot;)
            else:
                print(&quot;Killing process: &quot; + name + &quot; failed&quot;)
            return
 
    print(&quot;Not found process: &quot; + name)
 
def check_process_exist_by_name(name):
    for proc in psutil.process_iter():
        if proc.name() == name:
            return True
 
    return False
 
kill_by_process_name(&quot;iTunesHelper.exe&quot;)    
```

and then you could use the os module with &#39;taskkill&#39; to kill the task.

```
import os
 
def kill_by_process_name_shell(name):
    os.system(&quot;taskkill /f /im &quot; + name)
 
kill_by_process_name_shell(&quot;iTunesHelper.exe&quot;)
```

Referenced from [here](http://makble.com/kill-process-with-python-on-windows)

