You can use the [return-object][1] prop which will return the entire object of the selected item on selection.  
So, add this in `v-select` tag: 

    &lt;v-select 
        v-model=&quot;selectedRecipe&quot; 
        :items=&quot;recipe&quot; 
        item-text=&quot;name&quot; 
        item-value=&quot;duration&quot; 
        label=&quot;Select&quot; 
        return-object&gt;

And to print the values, you can do something like this:

    &lt;p class=&quot;answer&quot;&gt;Recipe applied to the group : {{selectedRecipe.name}}&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;p class=&quot;subtitle&quot;&gt;Duration: {{selectedRecipe.duration}}&lt;/p&gt;

Here is the [jsFiddle][2] for demo.


  [1]: https://vuetifyjs.com/en/components/selects#customized-item-text-and-value
